    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/355.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consular Agent <persName type="from">Hedian</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Esmeraldas</hi>
                        </placeName>, [<date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1914-02-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                            notBefore="1914-02-16T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">Undated</hi>
                        </date>
                        <hi rend="italic">; received February 17, 1914</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Bombardment ceased with destruction three houses. Others damaged, no lives lost.
                    Rebel forces intrenched sand beach Coquito. <pb facs="0387" n="271"
                        xml:id="pg_271"/> Few troops in city. Believe intelligent attack several
                    points would be success. Inhabitants neutral zone mile distant exposed to rain.
                    Many returning.</p>
                <closer>[Unsigned.] [<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hedian</hi>
                    </signed>.]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
